        <title>Activity: To use a series of techniques to be able to do calculations [LO 1.10]</title>
        <para id="id1164219154880">1. A pocket calculator is very helpful in calculating answers, but it is useless if one does not understand what one reads. Work with a friend. Follow the steps of the flow diagrams and draw a circle around the first correct answer. First make sure that you know what to do!</para>
